<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Letter of Appointment</title>
  <style>
    @page { size: A4; margin: 0; }

    body {
      font-family: "Calibri", Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #000;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .page {
      width: 210mm;
      height: 297mm;
      position: relative;
      page-break-after: always;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      padding: 40mm 25mm 25mm 25mm;
    }

    /* === Letterhead === */
    .letterhead {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 210mm;
      height: auto;
      z-index: -1;
    }

    /* === General Content Styling === */
    .content {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    .title {
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .date {
      text-align: right;
      font-size: 12px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .address-block {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    ol {
      margin-left: 20px;
      margin-top: 0;
      padding-left: 10px;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    /* === Signature === */
    .signature-block {
      margin-top: 25px;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .signature-block img {
      width: 110px;
      height: auto;
      margin-top: 6px;
      opacity: 0.95;
    }

    /* === Annexure / Salary Table === */
    .annexure-title {
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-top: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .salary-table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      width: 80%;
      margin: 0 auto;
      margin-top: 12px;
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .salary-table th,
    .salary-table td {
      border: 1px solid #000;
      padding: 6px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .salary-table th {
      background-color: #f3f3f3;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .note {
      font-size: 11px;
      margin-top: 18px;
      width: 80%;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }

    .note ul {
      margin-top: 6px;
      margin-left: 20px;
    }

    .page-break { page-break-after: always; }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 1 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %>
      <img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" alt="Letterhead" />
    <% } %>

    <div class="content">
      <p class="date"><%= appointment.issueDate || appointment.appointmentDate || "" %></p>

      <p class="title">Letter of Appointment</p>

      <div class="address-block">
        <strong>To,</strong><br/>
        <%= appointment.employeeName || "" %><br/>
        <%= appointment.address || "" %>
      </div>

      <p>Dear <strong><%= appointment.employeeName || "" %></strong>,</p>

      <p><strong>Sub: Your Career with AMAZON IT SOLUTIONS.</strong></p>

      <p>We are immensely pleased appointing you as a <strong><%= appointment.position || appointment.designation || "" %></strong>, and have you as a part of Amazon IT Solutions Family. We believe your potential skills will be a valuable contribution to our company.</p>

      <p><strong>Effective Date of Appointment:</strong> Your Date of Joining at <strong>“Amazon IT Solutions”</strong> is <strong><%= appointment.joiningDate || "" %></strong> and following are the terms and conditions:</p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Job Assignment:</strong>In your assignment you will be required to perform duties as laid down in the 
Job Description for your position.</li>
        <li><strong>Leave Entitlement:</strong>You will be entitled to leaves as per Amazon IT Solutions policy 
Mentioned in Rules and Regulations formulated in the Employee Hand Book of Amazon IT solutions 
from time to time.</li>
        <li><strong>Placement & Compensation:</strong> You will be placed in the appropriate responsibility level of the Company and will be entitled to total compensation of <strong>INR <%= appointment.ctc ? Number(appointment.ctc).toLocaleString('en-IN') : "" %> (<%= appointment.ctcWords || "" %>) Per Annum</strong>. Compensation will be governed by rules of the Company, as applicable and/or amended hereafter.</li>
      </ol>

      <p><strong>Note:</strong> Breakup of the fixed salary is as per the Annexure sheet.</p>

      <ol start="4">
        <li><strong>Statutory Deductions:</strong> Deductions, if any, will be made from your salary as per the prevailing law of the country. However, for your income tax you shall be personally responsible for filing returns etc. The company will provide you the tax deductions certificate, if applicable at the end of each financial year.</li>
        <li><strong>Code of Conduct:</strong> The Code of Business Conduct and Ethics helps to ensure compliance with legal requirements and our standards as approved by the Board from time to time formulated in the Employee Handbook of Amazon IT Solutions. All employees are expected to read and understand this Code, uphold these standards in day-to-day activities, comply with all applicable policies and adhere to these standards.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 2 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %><img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" /><% } %>
    <div class="content">
      <ol start="6">
        <li><strong>Posting & Transfer:</strong> Your initial posting will be at Hyderabad. However, your services are liable to be transferred, at the sole discretion of Management, to any department, location, associate, sister concern or subsidiary, at any place in India or abroad.</li>
        <li><strong>Probation:</strong> You will be on probation for a period of six months. The period of probation can be extended at the discretion of Management.</li>
        <li><strong>Full time employment:</strong> Your position is full-time employment with the Company and you shall devote yourself exclusively to the business and interests of the Company.</li>
        <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> You will not, at any time, during the employment or after, without consent of Management, disclose or divulge any information regarding the Company’s affairs or administration.</li>
        <li><strong>Intellectual Property:</strong> Any new method or design you conceive during your employment will remain the sole property of the Company.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 3 ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %><img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" /><% } %>
    <div class="content">
      <ol start="11">
        <li><strong>Responsibilities & Duties:</strong> Your work will be subject to company rules related to conduct, discipline, and performance. You must effectively perform to ensure results.</li>
        <li><strong>Past Records:</strong> If any declaration given or information furnished by you proves false, you will be liable for removal from service without any notice.</li>
        <li><strong>Termination of employment:</strong> During probation, services may be terminated by giving two months’ notice or gross salary in lieu thereof by the employer.</li>
        <li><strong>General Conditions:</strong> You must adhere to all company rules and avoid any unlawful or subversive activity while employed.</li>
        <li><strong>Non-Disclosure:</strong> You will not disclose by word or otherwise, any business plans, trade secrets, or confidential information of Amazon IT Solutions.</li>
        <li><strong>Acceptance:</strong> If you accept the above terms, please sign the photocopy of this Appointment Letter and return it. Otherwise, this offer will be withdrawn and cancelled.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="signature-block">
        <p>For Amazon IT Solutions,</p>
        <% if (signaturePath) { %><img src="<%= signaturePath %>" alt="Signature" /><% } %>
        <p><strong><%= appointment.hrName || "Chakravarthy Devarakonda" %></strong><br/><%= appointment.hrDesignation || "Manager – Human Resources" %></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== PAGE 4: ANNEXURE ===== -->
  <div class="page">
    <% if (letterheadPath) { %><img src="<%= letterheadPath %>" class="letterhead" /><% } %>

    <div class="content">
      <p><strong>Note:</strong> This is a computer-generated document. No Signature is required.</p>
      <p>This is to certify that I, <%= appointment.employeeName || "" %>, have read and understood all the above-mentioned terms and conditions and I hereby accept them without any duress or coercion.</p>

      <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Date: ____________ &nbsp;&nbsp; Place: ____________ &nbsp;&nbsp; Signature: ____________</p>

      <p class="annexure-title">Annexure-I</p>
      <p style="text-align:center; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:10px;">SALARY COMPUTATION</p>

      <table class="salary-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Components</th><th>Per annum</th><th>Per month</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <% (appointment.salaryComponents || []).forEach(function(row){ %>
            <tr>
              <td><%= row.label %></td>
              <td><%= row.perAnnum %></td>
              <td><%= row.perMonth %></td>
            </tr>
          <% }) %>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="note">
        <p><strong>Note:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Medical Insurance covers Rs.4 Lakhs for the employee and dependents.</li>
          <li>Personal Accident Insurance covers Rs.7.5 Lakhs for the employee.</li>
          <li>The LTA can be claimed against bills at the end of the financial year under the Income Tax Act.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
